This ridgeline plot then shows the distribution of the 75th percentile of earnings one year after graduation over different institutions. We see similar trends as in the previous graph, where the same degrees as before seem to have the most widely spread distributions. However, in general we observe that for each degree the 75th percentile earnings are more widely spread than the median earnings. This indicates that the awarding institution seems to be more important when considering the possibility for high earnings outcomes.
